# React Native SDK Conventions

## Tech Stack

TypeScript (strict), React Native Builder Bob, OpenTelemetry, Yarn workspaces

## Project Structure

```
pulse-react-native-otel/
├── src/                        # Library source
│   ├── index.tsx               # Public API — single Pulse facade
│   ├── config.ts               # SDK configuration / start
│   ├── trace.ts                # Span/tracing API
│   ├── events.ts               # Custom events
│   ├── errorHandler.ts         # Global error handler
│   ├── errorBoundary.tsx       # React ErrorBoundary component
│   ├── user.ts                 # User identification
│   ├── globalAttributes.ts     # Global attribute management
│   ├── initialization.ts       # Platform checks
│   ├── utility.ts              # Shared helpers
│   ├── pulse.interface.ts      # Shared types
│   ├── pulse.constants.ts      # Constants
│   ├── NativePulseReactNativeOtel.ts  # Codegen native module
│   ├── navigation/             # React Navigation integration
│   │   ├── index.ts            # Public exports
│   │   ├── navigation.interface.ts
│   │   ├── useNavigationTracking.ts
│   │   ├── screen-session.ts
│   │   ├── screen-load.ts
│   │   └── screen-interactive.ts
│   ├── network-interceptor/    # HTTP instrumentation
│   │   ├── initialization.ts
│   │   ├── request-tracker.ts
│   │   ├── request-tracker-xhr.ts
│   │   ├── span-helpers.ts
│   │   ├── url-helper.ts
│   │   ├── header-helper.ts
│   │   ├── graphql-helper.ts
│   │   └── network.interface.ts
│   └── __tests__/              # Unit tests
├── android/                    # Native Android module (Kotlin)
├── ios/                        # Native iOS module (ObjC/Swift)
├── plugin/                     # Expo config plugin
├── example/                    # Example app
└── expo-example/               # Expo example app
```

## Public API Pattern

The SDK exposes a single `Pulse` facade object from `src/index.tsx`:

```typescript
export const Pulse = {
  start, isInitialized, useNavigationTracking, markContentReady,
  trackEvent, reportException, trackSpan, startSpan,
  setGlobalAttribute, setUserId, setUserProperty, setUserProperties,
  ErrorBoundary, withErrorBoundary,
};
```

All new public methods must be added to this object.

## File Naming

| Type | Convention | Examples |
|------|------------|---------|
| Source files | camelCase | `errorHandler.ts`, `config.ts`, `globalAttributes.ts` |
| Interface files | `*.interface.ts` | `pulse.interface.ts`, `navigation.interface.ts` |
| Constants files | `*.constants.ts` | `pulse.constants.ts` |
| Test files | `*.test.ts` in `__tests__/` | `utility.test.ts`, `url-helper.test.ts` |
| Feature folders | kebab-case | `network-interceptor/`, `__tests__/` |
| React components | PascalCase | `ErrorBoundary` |
| Hooks | `use*` | `useNavigationTracking` |
| Codegen native module | PascalCase (exception) | `NativePulseReactNativeOtel.ts` |

## Feature Modules

Group related functionality into feature folders under `src/`:
- Each feature folder should have an `index.ts` for public exports
- Keep interfaces in `*.interface.ts` co-located with the feature
- Helper files use `*-helper.ts` naming

## Platform Guards

All native calls must be wrapped with `isSupportedPlatform()` from `initialization.ts`. Currently supports Android only (`Platform.OS === 'android'`). Native calls without this guard will crash on unsupported platforms.

## TypeScript Configuration

- `strict: true` — all strict checks enabled
- `noUncheckedIndexedAccess: true` — safe indexing
- `verbatimModuleSyntax: true` — explicit `import type`

## Span Types (`pulse.type`)

- `interaction` — critical user interaction spans
- `screen_session` / `screen_load` — screen tracking
- `app_start` — cold/warm start
- `device.anr` / `device.crash` / `non_fatal` — stability events
- `app.jank.frozen` / `app.jank.slow` — rendering performance
- `network.<status>` / `network.change` — network calls and connectivity
- `session.start` / `session.end` — session boundaries
- `custom_event` — developer-defined events
- `app.click` — touch/click events

## Span Attributes

Use `pulse.*` prefixed attributes for Pulse-specific data:
- `pulse.type` — categorizes the span
- `pulse.interaction.name`, `pulse.interaction.id`, `pulse.interaction.apdex_score`
- `screen.name`, `last.screen.name` — screen identifiers

## Resource Attributes

- `app.build_name` — app version (materialized as `AppVersion` in ClickHouse)
- `os.name` — platform (materialized as `Platform`)
- `os.version`, `device.model.name`, `rum.sdk.version`

## Best Practices

- All imports must be relative (`./`, `../`) — no path aliases in source
- Log messages must use `[Pulse]`, `[Pulse RN]`, or `[Pulse <Feature>]` prefixes
- Prettier: single quotes, 2-space indent, trailing commas (ES5) — configured in `package.json`
- No wildcard imports

## Code Quality

- **ESLint**: flat config (`eslint.config.mjs`), extends `@react-native`, Prettier as error
- **Lefthook**: pre-commit runs lint + typecheck, commit-msg runs commitlint
- **Commitlint**: `@commitlint/config-conventional` — all commits must be conventional

## Commands

```bash
yarn install                # install deps
yarn typecheck              # TypeScript check
yarn lint                   # ESLint
yarn test                   # unit tests (Jest)
yarn example start          # run example app
yarn example android        # run Android example
yarn example ios            # run iOS example
```

## Build

React Native Builder Bob for library builds. Supports both `example/` and `expo-example/` apps.

## Publishing

Automated via `.github/workflows/publish-react-native.yml`
